{"_id":"note:iNaDIpTzgo","title":"3. Props","content":"## Props\n\n\nThe component should receive a props parameter in order to map props\n\n```jsx\nimport React from 'react'\n\nexport default function Card(props) {\n    console.log(props);\n\n    return (\n        <div className=\"card\">\n            <img src={`../../public/${props.imageURL}`} alt=\"japan\"  />\n            <div className=\"card--info\">\n                <div className=\"card--location\">\n                    <img src=\"../../public/marker.svg\" alt=\"marker\" />\n                    <span className='card--country'>{props.location} </span>\n                    <a href={props.googleMap} target=\"_blank\">View on Google maps</a>\n                </div>\n                <h1 className='card--title'>{props.title}</h1>\n                <h3 className='card--date'>{props.startDate} - {props.endDate}</h3>\n                <p className='card--description'>{props.description}</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    )\n}\n```","tags":[],"folderPathname":"/ðŸ“˜ FrontEnd/REACT","data":{},"createdAt":"2022-08-05T02:51:16.440Z","updatedAt":"2022-08-05T02:54:36.634Z","trashed":false,"_rev":"lXSEeE6gZ"}